Always use type hints in JavaScript/TypeScript, follow Next.js best practices, ensure mobile-first design, and prioritize clean, maintainable code.

# Development Guidelines

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript for type safety when possible
- Follow Next.js 14 best practices and conventions
- Use functional components with hooks
- Implement proper error handling and loading states
- Write clean, readable, and maintainable code

## Design Principles
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Use Tailwind CSS for consistent styling
- Follow accessibility best practices (ARIA labels, keyboard navigation)
- Ensure smooth animations and transitions
- Maintain brand consistency with primary colors (teal #0D9488, blue #1D4ED8)

## Component Architecture
- Create reusable components
- Use proper prop validation
- Implement proper state management
- Follow React best practices for performance

## File Organization
- Keep components in the components/ directory
- Use lib/ for utility functions and data
- Organize pages in the pages/ directory
- Maintain clear separation of concerns

## Performance
- Optimize images and assets
- Use Next.js Image component when appropriate
- Implement proper loading states
- Minimize bundle size

## Testing
- Write unit tests for key components
- Test user interactions and form validation
- Ensure cross-browser compatibility
- Test responsive design on various screen sizes
